SIMPLE: seducer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seducer
<hw>Se*du"cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, seduces. For a female seducer, the term <er>seductress</er> is
also used</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>He whose firm faith no reason could remove,⟦br⟧
Will melt before that soft <qex>seducer</qex>, love.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>One who induces
another to engage in sexual intercourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seducible</ent>⟦br⟧
